{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.053Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scaling laws describe how "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "loss and capability improve predictably",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with more compute, data, and parameters. For agent builders choosing models and budgets, these relationships explain why larger models cost more but often plan and tool-call more reliably—and why inference cost scales with model size."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Empirical power-law relationships (Kaplan et al., Chinchilla et al.) show test loss decreases as:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "L \\approx A \\cdot N^{-\\alpha} + B \\cdot D^{-\\beta} + L_\\infty"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "where "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "N"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is parameters, "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "D"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " training tokens, and "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "L_\\infty"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " irreducible loss. Chinchilla argued optimal training uses ~20 tokens per parameter for compute-optimal models."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When selecting an agent backbone: doubling parameters often improves reasoning and format adherence, but inference price and latency rise too. Scaling laws guide whether to use a smaller fast model with RAG or a larger model with shorter prompts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Three axes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model size",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — more capacity to memorize patterns and rules"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Data",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — more diverse exposure; diminishing returns if model too small"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Compute",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — FLOPs tie N and D together in training budgets"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inference scaling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Decode cost per token roughly scales with parameter count and sequence length through attention and FFN. Agent systems feel this as API price per 1M tokens and max throughput."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits of understanding scaling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Predict quality jumps when upgrading model tier"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Justify budget for larger model on high-stakes agent paths"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Recognize when data quality beats raw size (fine-tuning laws differ from pre-training)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Laws are approximate; benchmarks saturate"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bigger models amplify alignment failures if mis-trained"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Edge deployment may forbid largest scales—quantization and distillation trade capability for size"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A tier-1 agent uses a 70B-class model for planning and a 8B model for subtasks—exploiting that not every step needs maximum scale. Routing by task difficulty is a practical response to scaling economics."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Emergent abilities (caution)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Some capabilities appear suddenly at scale on benchmarks, but \"emergence\" is debated—often measurement thresholds. Do not assume a small model will match a large one on complex multi-tool planning without empirical eval."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Loss improves predictably with parameters, data, and compute"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Chinchilla: balance model size and tokens for training efficiency"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent cost and quality trade off via model scale at inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluate agent tasks directly—scaling laws are guides, not guarantees"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
